OL,3,C'It felt inhumane' - Mum with full-
OL,4,Ctime job threatened with eviction twice
OL,6,F"It's a bit embarrassing, to be
OL,7,Fhonest. I would absolutely love a
OL,8,Fbedroom. Just my own space to chill
OL,9,Fout in."
OL,11,FAngela said half of her wages go
OL,12,Fstraight on rent, leaving her with
OL,13,Fonly #300 a month for food, gas,
OL,14,Felectric and travel.
OL,16,FWhen she and her children first moved
OL,17,Finto their current Solihull
OL,18,Faccommodation, they arrived to find no
OL,19,Felectricity, a broken boiler and no
OL,20,Fheating or hot water. It took five
OL,21,Fdays before repairs were carried out.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/10
