OL,3,C'It felt inhumane' - Mum with full-
OL,4,Ctime job threatened with eviction twice
OL,6,F"We should be out living life, but we
OL,7,Fcan't. When I got an email saying we
OL,8,Fwere being evicted again, I was at
OL,9,Fbreaking point. I didn't know how I
OL,10,Fcould keep going.
OL,12,F"When I spoke to Shelter, they were
OL,13,Fthe first people who really listened.
OL,14,FThey helped me stay in this property,
OL,15,Fjust knowing someone was there, took
OL,16,Fsome of the pressure off."
OL,18,FShelter's emergency helpline manager,
OL,19,FNadeem Khan, said Angela's experience
OL,20,Fis part of a much wider crisis.
