OL,3,C'It felt inhumane' - Mum with full-
OL,4,Ctime job threatened with eviction twice
OL,6,F"Every day, we hear from people living
OL,7,Fwith the constant fear that they could
OL,8,Flose their home the moment an eviction
OL,9,Fnotice drops through their letterbox.
OL,10,FMany are skipping meals just to cover
OL,11,Frent, cutting back on essentials, and
OL,12,Fmaking impossible choices simply to
OL,13,Fstay afloat."
OL,15,FA spokesperson for Solihull Community
OL,16,FHousing, which delivers housing
OL,17,Fservices on the council's behalf,
OL,18,Fsaid: "We always aim to secure
OL,19,Ftemporary accommodation in the
OL,20,Fborough, but this is not always
OL,21,Fpossible as demand exceeds supply.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G8/10
